---
import HermesLayout from "../../layouts/HermesLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/quickstart-shared.css";
---

<HermesLayout
  title="Hermes Agent Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes"
  description="Install Hermes Agent, configure it for your stack, and run your first autonomous multi-step coding task."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="qs-wrapper">

    <header class="qs-hero">
      <span class="qs-hero__eyebrow">Hermes Agent · Getting Started</span>
      <h1 class="qs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="qs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="qs-hero__desc">Autonomous multi-step coding agent with tool plugins and workflow planning. Describe what you want — Hermes plans and executes it, step by step.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="qs-journey">

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">01</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Prerequisites</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Node.js 18+ and a model API key</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Hermes works with Anthropic Claude, OpenAI, or any OpenAI-compatible provider. Have an API key ready.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>node --version</code></div>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">02</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Install</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Install Hermes Agent globally</h2>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>npm install -g hermes-agent</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Verify: hermes --version</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">03</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Configure</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Initialize in your project</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">This creates hermes.config.json in your project root. Edit it to tell Hermes about your stack, tools, and constraints — this is what makes it useful.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd-group">
          <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>cd your-project</code></div>
          <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>hermes init</code></div>
        </div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">The init wizard will ask about your stack and set sensible defaults.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step qs-step--active">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">04</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">First Run</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Ask what the codebase does</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Before running any task that modifies files, start by asking Hermes to understand the codebase. This gives you a baseline and lets Hermes build a plan.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>hermes "what does this codebase do and what are the main moving parts"</code></div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="qs-milestone">
      <span class="qs-milestone__eyebrow">First Real Task</span>
      <h2 class="qs-milestone__title">Always --dry-run before you execute</h2>
      <p class="qs-milestone__desc">Hermes is autonomous — it will make real changes. The --dry-run flag shows you the full execution plan before anything touches your files. Build this habit from day one.</p>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">1</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Write a specific task description. Specific = better plan.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">2</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Run with --dry-run first to preview the plan.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>hermes "write unit tests for src/utils/auth.ts — test all exported functions, edge cases included" --dry-run</code></div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">3</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Review the plan. If it looks right, run without --dry-run. If not, refine your task description and try again.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="qs-next">
      <p class="qs-next__title">What next?</p>
      <div class="qs-next__grid">
        <a href="/hermes-agent/tips/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚡</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Tips & Tricks</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Task descriptions, checkpoints, YAML workflows, tool plugins.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/hermes-agent/cheatsheet/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">📋</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Cheatsheet</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">All commands and flags at a glance.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/hermes-agent/changelog/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">🔔</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Changelog</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Every Hermes release, tracked.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/hermes-agent/configs/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚙️</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Configs</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">hermes.config.json reference, tool plugins.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('.qs-cmd').forEach(function(block) {
      var btn = document.createElement('button');
      btn.className = 'qs-cmd__copy';
      btn.textContent = 'copy';
      btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
        var code = block.querySelector('code');
        if (!code) return;
        var text = code.textContent.replace(/^\$\s*/, '').trim();
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(function() {
          btn.textContent = 'copied!';
          setTimeout(function() { btn.textContent = 'copy'; }, 1500);
        });
      });
      block.style.paddingRight = '5rem';
      block.appendChild(btn);
    });
  </script>
</HermesLayout>
